  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowerment of the Indigenous Communities in Nepal to Protect their Rights</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of the collaboration is two-fold:
1) At the local level, ensure that communities impacted by the accelerated investment in the hydropower sector understand their rights, have received trainings on various modes of available advocacy, and are able to submit a complaint - should they choose - to an accountability office for their grievances to be heard. The desired outcome is that any project impacting these communities move forward, if at all, only after consultation with the communities and in manner respectful of rights.

2) Increase LAHURNIP&apos;s capacity to serve indigenous communities in Nepal to challenge development projects that threaten rights, so as to prevent abuses and ensure that indigenous voices are part of decision-making around development.</narrative>
  </description>
